                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-259-off1482 t18200918-259-crimeloc1485"></join>. On the 9th of August, about half-past seven in the morning, a woman opposite said that a man<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182009180097"></xptr>has got a scarf from your shop. He had been in the shop just before. The shop was full of people. He passed me going out as she spoke. I looked at him, he walked away about two doors, I touched him on the shoulder and said he had something belonging to me, and asked him to come back - he did so. I put my hand in his outside coat pocket and took out the scarf. He fell on his knees and begged forgiveness.</p>
